4 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
5 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
6 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 5001 of Title 62, unless there
7 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
8 This act shall be known and may be cited as the "State Accounts
9 for Federal Expenditures Act" (SAFE Act).
10 SECTION 2. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
11 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 5002 of Title 62, unless there
12 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
13 As used in the State Accounts for Federal Expenditures Act:
14 1. "Agency" means any agency, board, bureau, commission, or
15 other entity organized within the executive department of state
16 government;
17 2. "Block grant" means a funding mechanism used by the federal
18 government that is not based on a program or an application; and
19 3. "Competitive grant" means a grant an agency applies for to
20 receive federal funding that is not necessarily associated with a
21 federal program the agency already operates.
22 SECTION 3. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
23 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 5003 of Title 62, unless there
24 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
HB1221 HFLR Page 2
BOLD FACE denotes Committee Amendments.

1 There is hereby created in the State Treasury "State Accounts
2 for Federal Expenditures" (SAFE Accounts). These accounts shall be
3 used by agencies for funds received under competitive grant awards,
4 direct monetary payments to the agency not associated with an
5 established federal program the agency operates, and block grants.
6 These accounts shall not be used for existing federal programs
7 agencies operate as of January 1, 2025, unless the program is a
8 competitive grant the agency must reapply for funds after November
9 1, 2025.
10 SECTION 4. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
11 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 5004 of Title 62, unless there
12 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
13 A. Beginning November 1, 2025, all agencies applying for
14 competitive grants through Grants.gov, or any of its successors,
15 shall submit to the Speaker of the Oklahoma House of
16 Representatives, the President Pro Tempore of the Oklahoma State
17 Senate, the Governor, the House Appropriations and Budget Chair, the
18 Senate Appropriations Chair, and the Secretary of Finance notice of
19 the application that includes, but is not limited to, the
20 application deadline, when the agency expects to hear it will be
21 receiving funds under the grant, what federal department, agency, or
22 other federal entity is awarding the grant, the amount of the grant,
23 the purpose of the grant, and for how many years the agency will
24 receive funding under the grant if it is awarded.
