4 SECTION 6. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
5 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 5006 of Title 62, unless there
6 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
7 A. Beginning July 1, 2025, if the federal government, through
8 legislation, directs that all federal funds to states are
9 appropriated as block grants instead of program-specific funding,
10 these funds shall be placed in SAFE Accounts created by the Office
11 of Management and Enterprise Services for the correct agency or
12 agencies that utilize the funds.
13 B. For federal programs that are already in existence, agencies
14 shall be able to access these funds immediately in order to prevent
15 a stop in service to the people of Oklahoma.
16 C. For both current and new programs, agencies shall submit
17 information as required under Section 34.36 of Title 62 of the
18 Oklahoma Statutes. Agencies shall also present such information as
19 required in Section 34.95 of Title 62 of the Oklahoma Statutes.
20 D. The Legislature may formally disapprove of an agency's use
21 of block grant funding through a concurrent resolution. If such
22 disapproval occurs, the agency shall inform its corresponding
23 federal entity of the disapproval and withdraw from receiving such
24 funds. If no action is taken by the Legislature on block grant
